    "text": "decision_d8f8761e-d67c-4d96-8217-3af3b67ec403 agent agent medium 2026-07-05T00:07:19.518Z 2026-07-05T00:07:19.518Z decision Keep experience lanes separated Prism serves both utility and experience, so runtime controls and bot orchestration can easily blur the purpose of each mode if they share too much surface behavior. Chat, Zen, Coffee, and Sandbox stay separated by server guardrails and UI expectations. Advanced runtime knobs belong in Sandbox, while companion and group-chat lanes preserve their own focused behavior. New features should choose the correct lane instead of becoming universal controls. This keeps user mental models understandable and helps agents avoid cross-mode regressions. AGENTS.md README.md apps/api/src/server.ts audience:all ux architecture"
